<div type="definition">
<p>COMPLETELY AND INTENSELY EXCELLENT.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for ultimate perfection is zhì 至 (ant.* liè 劣 "very inferior").</p>
<p>2. Jí 極 refers to the attainment of an ultimate point or an ultimate stage.</p>
<p>3. Jué 絕 focusses on the comparative aspect of excelling all others.</p>
<p>4. Yōu 優 (ant. liè 劣 "very inferior") focusses on the comparative aspect of excelling most others.</p>
<p>5. Quán 全 (ant. cán 殘 "seriously deficient") focusses on the complete presence of some conditions of excellence.</p>
        </div>
